<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68d9a6e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10701"><num value="10701">§ 10701.</num><heading> Application</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68d9a6f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10701/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><chapeau> Except as otherwise specifically provided, this chapter applies to a vessel on a voyage between—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf68d9a70-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10701/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a port of the United States and a port in a foreign country (except a port in Canada, Mexico, and the West Indies); and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf68d9a71-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10701/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> a port of the United States on the Atlantic Ocean and a port of the United States on the Pacific Ocean.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68d9a72-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10701/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> This chapter does not apply to a vessel on which a seaman by custom or agreement is entitled to share in the profit or result of a voyage.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68d9a73-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10701/c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content> This chapter does not apply to a foreign vessel.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf68d9a74-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/572">97 Stat. 572</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
